.TH "arm_iommu_map_sg" 9 "arm_iommu_map_sg" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
arm_iommu_map_sg \- map a set of SG buffers for streaming mode DMA
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" arm_iommu_map_sg
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct scatterlist *sg "  ","
.BI "int nents "  ","
.BI "enum dma_data_direction dir "  ","
.BI "unsigned long attrs "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
valid struct device pointer
.IP "sg" 12
list of buffers
.IP "nents" 12
number of buffers to map
.IP "dir" 12
DMA transfer direction
.IP "attrs" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Map a set of buffers described by scatterlist in streaming mode for DMA.
The scatter gather list elements are merged together (if possible) and
tagged with the appropriate dma address and length. They are obtained via
sg_dma_{address,length}.
